extends Node2D



@onready var sprite = $Sprite2D

func _ready():
	pass
func dprute_test():
	if Input.is_action_pressed("ui_accept"):
		sprite.visible = false
	elif sprite.visible == false and Input.is_action_pressed("ui_accept"):
		sprite.visible = true
	
	
		
		
'''The Core Godot Life Cycle
 
Your node lives in time.
These functions are the moments it is allowed to speak.

_ready() — Birth

Runs once when your node enters the scene tree.

Use it to:
• connect signals
• initialize variables
• set positions
• start timers
• prepare UI

Never put movement here.

_process(delta) — Heartbeat

Runs every frame.

Use it for:
• camera movement
• animations
• UI effects
• non-physics motion
• timers you manually count

delta keeps motion smooth.

_physics_process(delta) — Muscle memory

Runs at fixed 60 ticks/sec.

Use for:
• player movement
• gravity
• collisions
• anything touching physics

_input(event) — Nerves

Runs when input happens.

Use to:
• detect key presses
• mouse clicks
• gestures
• joystick

_exit_tree() — Death

Runs when the node is removed.

Use for:
• saving
• cleanup
• stopping music
• final signals
• freeing memory

Mini visualization

Birth → Life → Heartbeat → Muscles → Nerves → Death
That is literally your node’s lifecycle.'''
